The paper discusses dependencies between types in object-oriented software, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). The use of directed graphs to represent these dependencies suggests a possible connection to programming languages (cs.PL) and graph theory (cs.SI). The focus on the distribution of in-degree and out-degree suggests a possible connection to machine learning (cs.LG) and data analysis (cs.SD).
